	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Denekamp</placeName> the <date>5 December <hi rend="underline">1862</hi></date></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">My very dear uncle&#33;</p>
				<p>That you may receive these<lb/> rules in the best health is my<lb/> upright <sic>heartly</sic> wish.</p>
				<p>What is to me I find my as<lb/> well as possible thank God<lb/> and I hope to hear soon the same<lb/> from you my dear&#59; and I wish<lb/> at the same time that our heavenly<lb/> father may let us <sic>life</sic> in the<lb/> best health yet many years <del>good</del> together<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>.  My dear uncle&#63;  I have <del>M<add>&#63;</add></del> waited<lb/> already long at one letter from you<lb/> but in vain&#59; although I well<lb/> receive your book every month<lb/> which is also good but I beg you<lb/> friendly that you may satisfy on me request&#59;<lb/> and write me now a great letter<lb/> and you shall be assured that I<lb/> shall not be wanting to answer you<lb/> as soon as I have received your letter.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>My father goes the day after<lb/> tomorrow at <placeName><hi rend="underline">Hamburg</hi></placeName> he has<lb/> <del>th</del> do there any business and take<lb/> this letter and the cheeses which<lb/> you receive annexed this t<del>h</del>ill there&#59;<lb/> and I wish you of all my heart<del>h</del><lb/> that you <sic>my</sic> eat them in the best<lb/> health.  I look yet often on your<lb/> picture and as often as I regard it<lb/> I think I would you were by us&#58;<lb/> and wished well that it could be so&#44;<lb/> it should do me the greatest pleasure<lb/> what I could enjoy.</p>
				<p>The war which is by you caused<lb/> everywhere&#44; where are <sic>fabricks</sic><lb/> a great distress and bring about<lb/> much poverty&#59; give God that it<lb/> may be almost on the end&#59; then<lb/> unity makes power.</p>
				<p>Now my dear uncle&#33;  I know at<lb/> this time none news to write you&#44;<lb/> another time more.</p>
				<p>Be saluted many times from me<lb/> and in the hope to receive soon<lb/> a great letter from you&#59; I am and</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>I remain which the most respect<lb/>  Your <sic>affectionated</sic> niece till in eternity</p>
				<p><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">Jeanette Elkus</persName></hi></p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p> 
		</body>
